OL,4,Cbunting for 80th Liberation Day
OL,6,FMegs adds: "Rather than just flood the
OL,7,Ftown with red, white and blue ready-
OL,8,Fmade bunting, I thought it would be a
OL,9,Fbrilliant way to use up offcuts and
OL,10,Funwanted fabrics, rather than see them
OL,11,Fgoing to landfill.
OL,13,F"A perfect way to recycle and after
OL,14,Fall, it's just what would have
OL,15,Fhappened in 1945. Besides producing
OL,16,Fthe bunting, it is also an opportunity
OL,17,Ffor islanders from all walks of life,
OL,18,Facross the generations, to work
OL,19,Ftogether and feel a part of the
OL,20,FLiberation Day celebrations.
